<div>Screenshot comparisons are quite easy to implement.&nbsp;<span>they are&nbsp;done almost automatically.</span></div><div>In selenium there is the command 'captureEntirePageScreenshot'. The second parameter specifies the imagefilename. If a reference image exists, it will be automatically compared with the reference image.</div><div><br></div><div>All Screenshot comparisons are displayed below the bottom at the page.<br>The first column displays the recently captured image. The second column displays the reference image.</div><div>The third column displays the diff image, it will mark all&nbsp;differences in red&nbsp;<br><span><br>By clicking on the X, the images will be&nbsp;</span>deleted.</div><div>In the first picture there is also a checkmark. This action allows you to replace the current&nbsp;reference&nbsp;Image with the&nbsp;image&nbsp;<span>recently captured</span>.</div>